definitions.definition: A tuned electronic circuit used to generate a continuous output waveform .
An instrument for measuring rigidity by the torsional oscillations of a weighted wire .
A pattern that returns to its original state, in the same orientation and position , after a finite number of generations .

main_definition: A tuned electronic circuit used to generate a continuous output waveform .
secondary_definitions: An instrument for measuring rigidity by the torsional oscillations of a weighted wire .
